The global Crane Vessel Market is poised for steady growth, according to a report by Intel Market Research. The market was valued at USD 8.42 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 8.75 billion in 2026 to USD 12.15 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 4.2% during the forecast period. The increasing deployment of offshore wind farms, rising offshore decommissioning projects, and continued investments in offshore oil and gas infrastructure are driving demand for technologically advanced crane vessels across global markets.
Crane vessels play a critical role in offshore construction by enabling the installation, transportation, and removal of massive structures such as offshore wind turbine foundations, oil and gas platforms, subsea modules, and marine infrastructure. Growing renewable energy targets across Europe, Asia-Pacific, and North America have significantly increased the need for high-capacity heavy-lift vessels capable of supporting complex offshore engineering projects. At the same time, decommissioning aging offshore platforms is creating additional opportunities for specialized crane vessel operators.
